            "title": "Innovation of the Year",
            "description": "The Award was for the development of VECTor-6, a Broadband Photon Tomography device that enables researchers to perform an almost unlimited number of novel experiments for new discoveries. For example important PET isotopes that could not be imaged in a mouse at a sufficient resolution to quantify or clearly visualize uptake in tissue can be imaged at sub-mm resolution with VECTor-6, for example for 124-I with several times better resolution than state of-the-art coincidence PET. In addition, VECTor-6 uniquely enables to image thousands of tracer combinations simultaneously, resulting in a wealth of new accurate biological information that could not be obtained before. The new ultra-high resolution CT module that is integrated has the best characteristics for in-vivo imaging. Together with automated 3D Autoradiography and Optical Tomography options this has resulted in a Swiss Army Knife for Razor Sharp Synergistic Imaging.",
